The \fIWHEN\fR operation code is similar to the \fIWHEN\fRxx operation code in that it controls the processing of lines in a \fISELECT\fR operation\[char46] It differs in that the condition is specified by a logical expression in the indicator-expression operand\[char46] The operations controlled by the \fIWHEN\fR operation are performed when the expression in the indicator-expression operand is true\[char46] See Expressions for details on expressions\[char46] For information on how operation extenders M and R are used, see Precision Rules for Numeric Operations\[char46]


For more information, see Compare Operations or Structured Programming Operations\[char46]

.SH EXAMPLE
\fIWHEN\fR Operation
.PP
.nf
CL0N01Factor1+++++++Opcode(E)+Extended-factor2+++++++++++++++++++++++++++\[char46]\[char46]
 *
C                   SELECT
C                   WHEN    *INKA
C                   :
C                   :
C                   :
C                   WHEN    NOT(*IN01) AND (DAY = \[char39]FRIDAY\[char39])
C                   :
C                   :
C                   :
C                   WHEN    %SUBST(A:(X+4):3) = \[char39]ABC\[char39]
C                   :
C                   :
C                   :
C                   OTHER
C                   :
C                   :
C                   :
C                   ENDSL
.fi
